<head>SILVER</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">銀</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BRIGHT METAL [].</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for silver is yín 銀, but the word is not often used before Warring States times.</p>
<p>2. Wù 鋈 is an archaic word referring to silver ornaments used three times in SHI.</p>
        </div>
